  "id": "625c2861-0f13-5520-ac05-beecb2cfd4dc",
  "slug": "no-steam-easy-flan",
  "name": "No Steam Easy Flan",
  "recipe_type": "dessert",
  "brief_description": "Jelly flan using whole eggs.",
  "cuisine": "Filipino",
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Make the caramel by combining sugar and water in a saucepan. Apply heat. Continue cooking while stirring until the mixture thickens and the color turns medium brown. This is now the caramel."
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Pour the caramel into separate molds. (Note: you may use glass, metal, or ceramic baking pans as molds for the flan. Using ramekins is also a good idea.) Tilt the mold to spread caramel evenly. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Start making the flan by cracking the eggs into the bowl. Beat using a wire whisk. Gradually add sugar. Continue beating until mixture gets well blended. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Microwave \u00bc cup of the water for 35 seconds. Combine powdered gelatin and water. Mix well by stirring. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Pour milk into a pan. Apply heat until it goes into a simmer. (Note: do not apply too much heat. We want the milk to only be below boiling point)."
    },
    {
      "position": 6,
      "text": "Scoop around 5 to 6 tablespoons of warm milk (1 tablespoon at a time) into the bowl with sugar and eggs. Continue to stir the mixture. (Note: This process is also known as tempering. Two ingredients with different temperatures are gradually combined in order to slowly rise to the same temp.)"
    },
    {
      "position": 7,
      "text": "Pour the mixture from the bowl into the pan. Continue stirring until well blended."
    },
    {
      "position": 8,
      "text": "Gradually add gelatin mixture while stirring. Continue cooking in low heat for 1 minute. Turn off heat."
    },
    {
      "position": 9,
      "text": "Transfer mixture back to the bowl. Add all-purpose cream and vanilla extract. Stir until well blended. Remove bubbles by skimming."
    },
    {
      "position": 10,
      "text": "Pour the flan mixture into the molds. Cover each mold with aluminum foil or plastic wrap. Refrigerate overnight."
    },
    {
      "position": 11,
      "text": "Serve for dessert. Share and enjoy!"
    }
  ],
  "servings": 4,
